---
import { site } from '@/lib/site';
---

<section class="mx-auto max-w-prose px-4 pb-12 pt-16 sm:px-6 sm:pb-20 sm:pt-24 lg:px-8">
  <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-border bg-bg-subtle px-3 py-1 text-2xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-text-subtle">
    <span class="relative flex h-1.5 w-1.5">
      <span class="absolute inline-flex h-full w-full rounded-full bg-accent opacity-75 animate-ping"></span>
      <span class="relative inline-flex h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
    </span>
    Available for FAANG &amp; product-company conversations
  </div>

  <h1 class="mt-6 text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
    Hi, I&rsquo;m <span class="text-accent">Nikky</span>.
  </h1>

  <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-muted sm:text-xl">
    Backend engineer — <strong class="text-text font-medium">{site.role}</strong> at {site.company}, shipping backend
    for an adaptive learning platform used by <span class="text-text">500,000+ students</span>.
  </p>

  <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-muted sm:text-xl">
    I ship VS Code extensions, write C++ plugins for Unreal Engine, and build AI tooling
    ahead of the curve. When I find something annoying, I tend to build a tool instead of complain about it.
  </p>
</section>
